args:
For years, Sabnock gained power from darkness
in the hearts of children. Elias has been in the
grip of that darkness due to his voice changing
and tries to leave town—but he is reminded that
nothing changes if he does not face his fear.
The final battle with Sabnock is about to begin.
Oh, but this is terrible! Just terrible!
Ya learn somethin' about Sabnock there,\npolar bear? ...Heh. That rhymed.
We spoke again with children who recalled\nencounters with Sabnock.
And we realized there was a commonality\nin all of their stories.
All of them had ＂darkness＂ in their hearts.
Wanna run that by me again?
Jealousy, hatred... All the ugly parts of\na person comprise darkness.
A passion for music burns within each and\nevery child in the choir.

They compete with one another over it,
and in so doing raise each other to even
greater heights. It can be a wonderful
thing, and yet...
Well, sometimes the blaze of their passion\nflares up and consumes them.
If a person wishes to be better than a peer,\nthey sometimes want that peer to simply\ndisappear altogether.
I was once full of such envy for others.\nIt caused me no end of self-loathing.
Someone as accomplished as you felt\nthis way, Lucretia?
Of course. Now, as I grew into an adult,\nI became better able to control those\nfeelings, but...
Well, I still remember even now how dark\nand twisted my emotions were.
But what does the children's darkness have\nto do with Sabnock?

Well, I've got a theory. Suppose—and I'm
just spitballing here, so bear with me—
but suppose Sabnock first found the choir
here a hundred years ago.
It was just a normal-sized fiend back then,\nbut in the century since, it got bigger.\nLike, a LOT bigger.
Maybe it's been drawing strength from the\ndarkness in the children's hearts for all\nthis time.
Hmm. I see where you're going with this.\nHowever...
St-stay back! I'm leaving this town forever!
No! If I'm gone, that will be the end of\nthis entire thing!
There you are! Are you okay, Elias?
Ugh... Why am I always tripping\nover things?!
Can you get up? Here, give me your hand.
Because this is all my fault.
That thing told me to ＂get rid of it.＂\nIt gave voice to things I was thinking.
Get rid of it... Wait, you mean the choir?\nBut you're their best singer—why would\nyou want to do something like that?
I'm going to lose my voice.\nIt's coming any day now.
I figured as much. Your voice is changing.

A little while before the recital, I started
having a hard time hitting high notes.
I kept thinking it was just a frog in my
throat or something, but...it wasn't.
I'd hate it if I couldn't be in the\nchoir anymore, so that's why I\nhid it from everyone.
Then I started to get jealous of all the kids\nwho could still sing. ...Wildly jealous.

And somewhere in my heart, I started
to think that if this was a world where I
wouldn't be able to sing, I just wanted
the entire thing to go away.
The moment I thought that, the thing\nshowed up in my dream.
It said it wanted the power of darkness,\nso it absorbed it from my heart.
It used that darkness to get stronger,\nwhich means this is all my fault!
Not just you, Elias—there are lots of other\nchildren who share the same darkness.
Indeed, I am also one who gave strength\nto that fell beast.
That monster is going to use my darkness\nand there's nothing I can do about it!
What you do from here depends on you.\nYou—and you alone—must choose.
Do you leave Sabnock alone and flee,\nor do you face your darkness and best it?\nYou must choose.
I did not face my darkness. I chose to run.\nI gave up singing and I found a new path,\nwhich led me to conducting.
So running away is not an altogether bad\nidea. Is that what you wish to do?
Will you be satisfied to leave this village\nand never lift your voice in song again?
Then the path you must choose is clear.
Thank you, Vixel. Thank you.\nOh, I'm so sorry for everything.
I'm going to face my darkness. If I can't\novercome it, I'm never going to be able\nto continue singing.
I'm not going to run any more. Not from\nmy future, or from Sabnock!
Please let me help you defeat Sabnock,\n{player_name}!
I know I may not be much of a fighter,\nbut this is still MY fight.
I have to defeat Sabnock myself. I'll face\nit again and again until my darkness is\nbanished forever!
No, Elias. You won't face this alone.\nWe're going to take Sabnock down\ntogether.
We may be fighting a fiend, but we're\nalso fighting the darkness of all the\nchildren that fed it!
